  "prompt": "What is the limit to follow in Instagram?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Instagram has several limits to ensure the platform's integrity and prevent abuse or spam. Here are some of the key limits:\n\n1. **Following Limits**: \n   - You can follow up to 7,500 accounts in total.\n   - There are hourly and daily limits to how many accounts you can follow. The exact numbers can vary but typically, you should not follow more than 200 accounts per day to avoid being flagged as spam.\n\n2. **Likes**: \n   - You can like approximately 1,000 posts per day.\n\n3. **Comments**: \n   - Instagram limits comments to roughly 200 per day.\n\n4. **Direct Messages**: \n   - There are limits on how many direct messages you can send per day, generally around 100 messages.\n\n5. **Posting Frequency**: \n   - There is no strict limit on how often you can post, but posting too frequently in a short period might flag your account for spam.\n\n6. **Hashtags**: \n   - You can use up to 30 hashtags per post.\n\nPlease note that these limits can change, and Instagram's algorithms may adjust based on user behavior and account activity. If you exceed these limits, you might face temporary restrictions or account suspension. Always try to engage authentically with content to avoid any issues.",
